<title>INDIA: India Infosys 96/97 net up at 369.8 mln rupees.</title>
<headline>India Infosys 96/97 net up at 369.8 mln rupees.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-04-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year to March 31, 1997</p>
<p>	    (in million rupees unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net profit		 369.8    vs	210.1</p>
<p>    Total revenue	  1,438.1    vs	934.1</p>
<p>    Expenditure		924.3    vs	571.8</p>
<p>    Interest		     6.1    vs	 nil</p>
<p>    Depreciation	     105.2    vs	 86.3</p>
<p>    Tax			   55.4    vs	 43.1</p>
<p>    Extraordinary income    35.9    vs	 nil</p>
<p>    Dividend (in percent)   55.0    vs	 50.0</p>
<p>Note - Software maker Infosys Technologies Ltd said total revenue included export income of 1.25 billion rupees (803.4 million in 1995/96), domestic sales of 139.4 million (82.1 million) and other income of 45.9 million (48.6 million).</p>
<p>The year's net profit included extraordinary income of 35.9 million rupees, it received for transfer of its WMS Yantra to its subsidiary Yantra Corporation.</p>
<p>The company set a final dividend of 40 percent against 35 percent a year ago. It already paid an interim of 15 percent versus same.</p>
<p>The company also announced a bonus equity issue of one share for every share held.</p>
<p>It has convened an annual general meeting of shareholders on June 7, 1997. The latest results are audited.</p>
<p>--Bombay Newsroom +91-22-265-9000</p>
